    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Visegrádská skupina"@cs, "Visegrádi grupp"@et, "Grupa Wyszehradzka"@pl, "Visegrad Group"@en, "Višegradska skupina"@hr, "Grupo de Visegrad"@es, "Visegrádi csoport"@hu, "Вишеградска група"@sr, "Grúpa Visegrad"@ga, "Grupp ta’ Visegrad"@mt, "Ομάδα Βίσεγκραντ"@el, "Вишеградската група"@bg, "Višegrado grupė"@lt, "Grupul de la Visegrád"@ro, "Visegrád-Gruppe"@de, "Visegrádgroep"@nl, "Gruppo di Visegrad"@it, "Grupo de Visegrado"@pt, "Groupe de Visegrad"@fr, "Visegradgruppen"@sv, "Visegradgruppen"@da, "Visegrad-ryhmä"@fi, "Višegradas grupa"@lv, "Višegrajska skupina"@sl, "Vyšehradská skupina"@sk;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Visegrad Group (Visegrad Four) is an alliance of four Central European states – Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland and Slovakia – for the purposes of furthering their European integration as well as advancing their military, economic and energy cooperation with one another."@en;
