    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Council of Arab Economic Unity (CAEU) was founded by Egypt, Iraq, Jordan, Kuwait, Libya, Mauritania, Palestine, Saudi Arabia, Sudan,Tunisia, Syria, United Arab Emirates and Yemen on June 3, 1957. It became effective on May 30, 1964 with the goal of achieving economic unity among its member states."@en;
