    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Амнести интернашонал"@sr, "Διεθνής Αμνηστία"@el, "Amnistía Internacional"@es, "Amnesty International"@ro, "Amnesty International"@hr, "Amnesty International"@sk, "Amnesty International"@de, "Amnesty International"@mt, "Amnesty International"@fi, "Amnesty International"@is, "Amnesty International"@it, "Amnesty International"@sl, "Amnesty International"@cs, "Amnesty International"@fr, "Uluslararası Af Örgütü"@tr, "Amnesty International"@lv, "Amnesty International"@da, "Amnesty International"@en, "Amnesty International"@ga, "Tarptautinė amnestija"@lt, "Amnesty International"@hu, "Amnesty International"@sv, "Amnistia Internacional"@pt, "Amnesty International"@nl, "Amnesty International"@pl, "Амнести Интернешънъл"@bg, "Amnesty International"@et;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Amnesty has grown from seeking the release of political prisoners to upholding the whole spectrum of human rights. Our work protects and empowers people – from abolishing the death penalty to protecting sexual and reproductive rights, and from combatting discrimination to defending refugees and migrants’ rights."@en, "Amnesty a commencé par demander la libération des prisonniers politiques. Elle a maintenant élargi son action à la défense de tous les droits humains: la protection et l’autonomisation des personnes ; l’abolition de la peine de mort, la protection des droits sexuels et reproductifs ; du combat contre les discriminations à la défense des droits des réfugiés et des migrants."@fr;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "AI"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "COB0001174"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "AI"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "AMNESTY"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#FD_050>;
