    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) is a free trade area with twenty member states. COMESA agreed to an expanded free-trade zone including members of two other African trade blocs and it is also considering a common visa scheme to boost tourism."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "CMESA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "COB0001032"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "CMESA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>;
